com.isbx.androidtools.networking

Interface UploadManager.UploadListener

  • Enclosing class:
    UploadManager

    public static interface UploadManager.UploadListener
    A listener interface to receive completion, error, and progress events during an upload request

    • Method Detail

      • onProgress

        void onProgress(int progress)

        This method is invoked whenever an individual file has finished uploading. The progress is an integer representation from 1 - 100 of how many files have been uploaded using the following formula: 

         progress = numberOfFilesUploaded / totalNumberOfFiles * 100;

        If only one file is being uploaded, this will only be called once with a progress of 100.

        Parameters:
        progress - The completion progress of the current upload request, as an integer in the range 1 - 100

      • onUploadComplete

        void onUploadComplete(String[] urls)
        This method is invoked once all files in the current request have been successfully uploaded. This will be called immediately after the last call to onProgress(int)
        Parameters:
        urls - A String array containing the S3 urls for each uploaded file, in the same order that the files were provided to the UploadManager

      • onUploadFailed

        void onUploadFailed(Throwable error,
                    int failureIndex)
        This method is invoked when a file upload fails
        Parameters:
        error - A Throwable provided by the networking library indicating why the upload failed
        failureIndex - The index of the file that failed to upload
